      b) Assets may not be redistributed or used in contexts unrelated to the Software.
            i) Assets are permitted to be used in Modified-Software.

      c) The copyright holder retains the right to grant exceptions to these conditions to individuals or
         entities.

2. Distribution of Modified-Software is permitted, subject to the following conditions:
      a) The Modified-Software must contain prominent notices that it has been modified from the original
         Software, on both:
            i) Within the Modified-Software itself.
            ii) On any webpage where the source or binary of the Modified-Software are distributed or hosted.

      b) Any attribution notices within the Software must remain in the Modified-Software.

      c) Webpages hosting the Modified-Software must contain a prominent hyperlink leading to a webpage
         (posted or owned by the copyright holder) hosting the Software.

